"As soon as you have conceived, your body starts preparing you for  
pregnancy. These things usually happen without you noticing as they are  
happening within your body - your uterus is starting to enlarge and soften
 
and your cervix is changing texture. Some women instinctively know when  
they are pregnant (especially recognizing the signs earlier in subsequent 

pregnancies) but for other women the early pregnancy symptoms might not be
 
so obvious."
